name: Web Development
description: This course provides an introduction to full-stack web development, covering front-end and back-end technologies, databases, and deployment strategies.

name: Data Structures
description: An in-depth study of data structures such as arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, and graphs, with an emphasis on algorithms and efficiency.

name: AI Basics
description: An introductory course on artificial intelligence, exploring topics such as machine learning, neural networks, and ethical considerations in AI.

name: Networking
description: A comprehensive study of computer networks, including network protocols, TCP/IP, network security, and cloud-based networking solutions.

name: Database Management
description: Covers the fundamentals of database management systems, SQL, NoSQL, indexing, normalization, and data security.

name: Cloud Computing
description: Introduces cloud computing concepts, including virtualization, cloud architecture, cloud services, and deployment models.

name: Cybersecurity
description: Focuses on the fundamentals of cybersecurity, covering cryptography, ethical hacking, security policies, and risk management.
